result.name: Tam Chai Yunnan Noodles

reviews.text: You pay for what you get. The taste is ok and the variety is enough.

The soup is good. The tofu and vegetables too. Downside - The pork belly is a bit old. It has a taste that reminds you of a sandwich you left in your school bag for a week. 

And they have a less noodle option. (Finished my veggies first. I’m a good boy.)
Nice noodle soup restaurant with varieties of topping and soup based to choose from.
Rather expensive for quality and amount of food
Good value, reliable and good choice of ingredients for noodles

result.name: 譚仔雲南米線

reviews.text: 呢間譚仔有個職員唔識譚仔話😂係後生仔黎
最難食嘅一間譚仔，個酸辣湯臭嘅
You pay for what you get. The taste is ok and the variety is enough.
對呢間譚仔嘅印象唔係幾好，上菜時間好鬼慢，我食開大辣，都唔辣嘅，不過啲湯都唔錯，比譚仔三哥貴幾元，份量又少，我寧願行多幾步去佐敦道46號食譚仔三哥好過
依間普通，小辡唔辡。
